column2: b"@PythiaR $JBGS is 30% MF on its way to 50%, but think their execution (getting $AMZN HQ2) and capital allocation as an independent company has been very strong (issued stock in the $40's, bought back mid $20's), has a deep mgt team, big development pipeline concentrated in NoVa."

b"@AustinValue if you're replacing your exposure to what $BPY owned, I'm not your guy to ask on malls (i'd just yolo some $MAC / $SPG calls w/ no work) or London office. NYC office: think $PGRE and $VNO are best r/r but less excited about them than once was. $JBGS is my biggest RE position but"
